Scheme name:
  dilithium3

Status:
  Provisional

Applications/protocols that use this scheme name:
  The Dilithium3 post-quantum blockchain protocol uses this URI
  scheme for:

  1. Certification verification links:
     dilithium3:verify?hash=<sha256-hex>&chain=30939

  2. Block and transaction references:
     dilithium3:tx/<transaction-hash>
     dilithium3:block/<block-number>

  3. Wallet and account addresses:
     dilithium3:<hex-address>?chain=30939

  4. Certification request initiation:
     dilithium3:certify?hash=<sha256-hex>&worm=true

  5. Finality proof references:
     dilithium3:proof/<block-number>

  The protocol is a post-quantum blockchain using NIST FIPS 204
  (ML-DSA-65, Security Level 3) digital signatures for document
  certification and immutability verification. It serves government,
  military, financial, and enterprise clients requiring quantum-
  resistant cryptographic guarantees.

  Chain ID: 30939
  Port: 30939/tcp+udp (IANA registration pending, ticket #1448192)
  Consensus: 24-validator Byzantine Fault Tolerant, 2-second blocks
  Production status: deployed January 2026, 2.8M+ blocks, 300M+
  documents certified

