ADDITIONAL CONTEXT
------------------

The dilithium3 URI scheme follows the pattern established by
existing blockchain URI schemes in the IANA registry:

  bitcoin:     (Provisional, registered)
  bitcoincash: (Provisional, registered)
  ethereum:    (Provisional, registered)
  starknet:    (Provisional, registered)

The dilithium3 scheme is distinguished from these by its use of
post-quantum cryptography (NIST FIPS 204 ML-DSA-65), making it
the first quantum-resistant blockchain URI scheme in the registry.

URI SYNTAX
----------

  dilithium3:<path>[?<query>]

  Examples:

  Verify a certified document:
dilithium3:verify?hash=a5b9d68fe1a8e54a72b9d41e1e7b98f2c6e3d5a4f8b7c2e1d3a9f5b6c8e4d7a2&chain=30939

  Reference a transaction:
dilithium3:tx/0x7739c81feb259ebfb19c94ed4063d0912660ad167e547ebc624500e0f8f38c97

  Reference a block:
    dilithium3:block/2844110

  Address with payment request:
dilithium3:0xBfFA8cf0E2B2698B833DCd0736034A40ab27F4fF?amount=100&chain=30939

  Request certification:
dilithium3:certify?hash=<sha256>&worm=true&tier=standard

  View finality proof:
    dilithium3:proof/2844110